ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Good to have an introduction to algebraic topology before. Otherwise, the beginning can be a bit harsh and some additional time should be spent on self-studies of the first few topics.
You probably have to take this if you're thinking about it.
I do not even need to recommend it as any other mathematician would simply have to take this course for their own knowledge.
It was interesting. I would recommend it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I gained some intuition and ideas how to apply algebraic topology to different areas in my discipline.
I already took a course in algebraic topology before, so it did not deepen my knowledge all that much.
